    "The Welch statistic was chosen because the homogeneity assumption was not met, but the normality assumption was met.",
    "The Welch One-Way ANOVA test results show significant differences between universities in all observed variables, namely MCT, SMT_Content, SMT_Style, SMT, and Overall_Score (p<0.05).",
    "It means there are significant differences in scores between universities in all aspects measured.",
    "In addition, the Fisher's test results also show significant differences between universities for all variables.",
    "It confirms the findings from the Welch One-Way ANOVA test that there are significant differences in university scores."
